| 
|  ??? sudo apt-get install r-base r-recommended

That is normal.

r-base does not depend on r-recommended, but suggests it.

r-recommended however does depend on a given version of R, and apt just tells
you that _given that you have r-recommended installed_ it can not upgrade
r-base. As such your request of 'install me just r-base, please' was not
satisfiable.

I keep forgetting which of the two deals smoothly with it, but between
'apt-get dist-upgrade' and 'apt-get update' one does; I think it is the
former which I use way more.

Hth, Dirk
